#Text=Watsonville
#Text=Watsonville is a city in Santa Cruz County in California in the Monterey Bay Area .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Santa Cruz Metro provides service from Santa Cruz and other towns around it , and Monterey-Salinas Transit provides service from destinations including Monterey and Salinas .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Downtown is pedestrian friendly .
#Text=There are some bicycle and pedestrian paths along the creeks , rivers , and sloughs around Watsonville as well and some limited bus service .
#Text=Taxi 's are available throughout the area by phone .
#Text=Watsonville airport also provides small craft access .
#Text=See
#Text=Mountains
#Text=Pajaro River
#Text=Mount Madonna
#Text=Auto races at Ocean Speedway .
#Text=Sunset State Beach , 201 Sunset Beach Rd ( The beach is 16 miles south of Santa Cruz .
#Text=Take Highway 1 , exit on San Andreas Road , and follow signs south . ) , ☏ +1831 763-7062 , toll-free : +1-800-444-7275 ( Reservations ) .
#Text=Day use
#Text=open daily 8AM to 1/2 hour after sunset .
#Text=Campground open year-round ( reservations recommended). .
#Text=The beach features pine trees , mountainous sand dunes , and ocean side picnic spots .
#Text=Bordered by large agricultural fields west of the city of Watsonville , the beach is a year-round destination for thousands of visitors .
#Text=Amenities include : Picnic tables , Camping areas ( including large group camping ) , Restrooms , and Showers ( Camping showers are 25 cents ; bring quarters . ) .
#Text=Food , lodging and supplies are available nearby .
#Text=The campground is open year-round .
#Text=There are 91 camping sites , one bicycle site and one group site .
#Text=Cost is $ 35 per night .
#Text=Call 800-444-7275 for reservations .
#Text=Campsites in the Dunes and Pine Hollow loops are first-come , first-serve during the winter ( Nov. 1 to the end of February ) .
#Text=Nature walks on the dunes and family programs are offered ; call the park for more information .
#Text=More information :
#Text=More information : http://www.parks.ca.gov/pages/544/files/Sunset-ManresaWebBrochure2012.pdf
#Text=Manresa State Beach , 1445 San Andreas Rd ( From Highway 1 , south of Aptos , take San Andreas Road southwest and continue for three miles to Manresa State Beach .
#Text=It is the first beach access you will reach on the coast . ) , ☏ +1 831-724-3750 .
#Text=Open daily sunrise to sunset , year round. .
#Text=Manresa State Beach features a beautiful expanse of sea and sand , with surf , fishing , surfing , and recreation .
#Text=Amenities include : Restrooms , Outdoor shower , Food
#Text=Dogs are allowed on the beach on leash .
#Text=Fire rings are available for beach fires .
#Text=More information :
#Text=More information : http://www.parks.ca.gov/pages/544/files/Sunset-ManresaWebBrochure2012.pdf $ 10 day use parking fee .
#Text=Pinto Lake County Park , 757 Green Valley Rd ( From Highway 1 south , exit onto Airport Boulevard , on Green Valley Road
#Text=make a left .
#Text=From Highway 1 north , take the Airport Boulevard exit , turn left onto Airport Blvd to Green Valley Road , go left .
#Text=You will go past Pinto Lake City Park and will see Pinto Lake County Park .
#Text=Make a left turn into the park . ) , ☏ +1 831-454-7956 , ✉ reservations@scparks.com .
#Text=Reservation hours are available daily from 10AM to 7PM during summer months .
#Text=Reservation end time varies according to season .
#Text=Drop in
#Text=park use is open daily from dawn to dusk. .
#Text=A 183 acre regional park , which features a scenic lake with a fishing pier and surrounding nature trails , playground , two family picnic areas , and wheelchair accessible restrooms .

#Text=Turtle Dove , a public art project by artist Roberto Castro and youth from the JTPA program , can be found at the park ; trail markers highlight the wildlife which can be viewed along the nature trail .
#Text=Soccer fields and two pavilions with BBQs are available for rent .
#Text=There is also a small baseball field .
#Text=See the location where locals believe the Virgin Mary appeared .
#Text=A disc golf course is the newest attraction to Pinto Lake Park .
#Text=Reservable picnic areas :
#Text=Reservable Picnic Areas Pavillions A and B are perfect outdoor locations for family and company picnics .
#Text=Available by reservation only .
#Text=They offer privacy for your group and a comfortable , scenic oasis for your enjoyment .
#Text=Capacity is 100 .
#Text=1 Large Barbecue and picnic tables are included .
#Text=Pavillion A is the first covered picnic area upon entering the park .
#Text=It is closest to the playground and near public restrooms .
#Text=Pavillion B is the second covered picnic area located at the far end of the park .
#Text=Public restrooms are nearby .
#Text=It offers privacy for your group .
#Text=Reservations can be made up to one year in advance .
#Text=Walk-in reservations can be made at the Simpkins Family Swim Center at 979 17th Avenue , Santa Cruz .
#Text=Office hours are Monday through Friday from 9AM- 4PM .
#Text=Please allow one month before event date for phone reservations , and 3 days for walk-in .
#Text=Cash , check or Visa/Mastercard accepted .
#Text=For more information , call ( 831)454-7956.
#Text=Pinto Lake Park , 451 Green Valley Rd
#Text=( Traveling North on HWY 1 from Monterey : Take Green Valley Road exit and follow for 3 Miles .

#Text=Traveling South on HWY 1 from Santa Cruz : Take HWY 152 Watsonville/Gilroy exit , Then IMMEDIATELY left onto Green Valley Rd . and travel 2.6 Miles inland . ) , ☏ +1831 722-8129 , ✉ pintolakepark@gmail.com .
#Text=Pinto Lake City Park is owned by the City of Watsonville and offers RV camping .
#Text=Amenities :
#Text=Back-in Sites 50 ' x 15 ' On grass
#Text=Electricity ( 30 amp )
#Text=City water Sewer
#Text=Wi-fi ( Strong , reliable signal ) Locked gate at night ( You get a key . )
#Text=Fire rings allowed in picnic area adjacent to campground Showers , laundry Rates :
#Text=Two adults in one RV or trailer : $ 35.00
#Text=One tow vehicle : Free
#Text=Children 16 and under : Free
#Text=Extra adults : $ 2.00 each
#Text=Dogs : $ 2.00 each
#Text=Extra vehicles : $ 2.00 each
#Text=Wetlands of Watsonville , 30 Harkins Slough Rd , ☏ +1831 768-1622 .
#Text=The City of Watsonville 's nature trails provide easy public access to this 800 acre freshwater wetland .

#Text=More than six miles of paved trails and 29 trail entrances in Watsonville neighborhoods offer new opportunities to enjoy the natural beauty of our special wetlands for recreation and relaxation .
#Text=The Wetlands of Watsonville Nature Center offers trail maps and other information about the animals and habitats of the area .
#Text=City wetland trails are free to use and open every day in every season .
#Text=Joggers , hikers , cyclists and birders are welcome to access any of the trails .
#Text=Several trails are wheelchair accessible ; please see trail maps for appropriate entrances .
#Text=Recommended Trail Walks & Entrances
#Text=Watsonville Slough Trail
#Text=Trail Head :
#Text=Park at the Wetlands of Watsonville Nature Center – 30 Harkins Slough Road , Watsonville , CA.(831)768-1622. Trail map available outside Nature Center .
#Text=Trail entrance behind center .
#Text=Approximate walk : 1.5 miles
#Text=Ohlone Loop Trail
#Text=Trail Head :
#Text=Park in the back of the West Marine parking lot by trail head – 500 Westridge Drive , Watsonville , CA .
#Text=Approximate walk : 1.5 miles
#Text=Upper Struve Slough Trail
#Text=Trail Head :
#Text=Park in Body Zone parking lot by trail head – 1810 Main Street , Watsonville , CA .
#Text=Approximate walk : 1.5 miles
#Text=Nearby Areas : Food and shopping center on Main Street .
#Text=Santa Cruz County Fairgrounds & Event Center , 2601 E. Lake Ave
#Text=( From Highway 1 , take Airport Blvd to East Lake Blvd ; turn left on East Lake and the Fairgrounds will be on your left-hand side . ) , ☏ +1 831-724-5671 .
#Text=Home of the Santa Cruz County Fair held each September and the races at the Ocean Speedway , Agricultural History Project and Museum and the historic Rogers House .
#Text=Henry J. Mello Center for Performing Arts , 250 East Beach St
#Text=( From Highway 1 , take the CA-152 E/Main Street exit toward Watsonville/Gilroy ; turn left on East Beach Street . ) , ☏ +1 831-763-4047 , ✉ mellocenter@charter.net .
#Text=This premier concert performance hall boasts the best acoustics in the county .
